At Manual Enumeration we use command :

whoami : Confirmed the current user.
id : Checked for interesting group memberships.
sudo -l : Checked if the current user can run any command as root without a password.
hostname : return the hostname of the target machine
uname -a: Checked the Kernel version for potential exploits.
cat /proc/version : may give you information on the kernel version and additional data such as whether a compiler (e.g. GCC) is installed.
cat /etc/issue : This file usually contains some information about the operating system but can easily be customized or changed. 
cat /etc/passwd file can be an easy way to discover users on the system.
